WEBVTT

00:00.024 --> 00:04.972
♪ Hey, why is it happening ♪

00:05.944 --> 00:08.652
♪ My heart is racing ♪

00:09.784 --> 00:13.792
♪ The world has fallen silent ♪

00:13.816 --> 00:18.572
♪ Hey, when I imagine you ♪

00:19.608 --> 00:22.636
♪ What kind of look ♪

00:23.640 --> 00:27.584
♪ Attracted me to you ♪

00:27.608 --> 00:30.880
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

00:30.904 --> 00:34.368
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

00:34.392 --> 00:39.640
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

00:39.640 --> 00:41.258
♪ I love you ♪

00:41.258 --> 00:44.736
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

00:44.760 --> 00:48.032
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

00:48.056 --> 00:53.728
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

00:53.752 --> 00:55.096
♪ I love you ♪

00:55.096 --> 00:58.432
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

00:58.456 --> 01:01.804
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

01:01.912 --> 01:07.109
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

01:07.109 --> 01:08.792
♪ I love you ♪

01:08.792 --> 01:12.192
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

01:12.216 --> 01:15.616
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

01:15.640 --> 01:21.216
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

01:21.240 --> 01:24.652
♪ I love you ♪

01:26.930 --> 01:27.720
=Love Me, Love My Voice=

01:27.720 --> 01:30.940
=Love Me, Love My Voice=
=Episode 22=

01:31.592 --> 01:34.812
(- I can't sleep.
- You're also scared of the storm?)

01:36.571 --> 01:38.268
The rain is so heavy.

01:38.811 --> 01:41.431
Yeah, but I kind of like rainy days.

01:42.571 --> 01:43.750
What do you think?

01:54.210 --> 01:55.231
Almost there.

01:56.092 --> 01:58.262
There are two school buses
back to school every afternoon.

01:58.262 --> 01:59.793
It's about ten more minutes.

02:00.133 --> 02:01.233
No rush.

02:01.853 --> 02:03.112
Just wait patiently.

02:12.973 --> 02:15.148
I remember when I was young,

02:15.172 --> 02:18.989
bus stations were just poles and signs.

02:19.013 --> 02:21.952
There was no rain shield.

02:30.772 --> 02:35.908
Do you get home from my school easily?

02:35.932 --> 02:38.712
I'll go straight
to the recording studio.

02:39.013 --> 02:44.112
Getting a taxi can be tricky,
but that's OK.

02:48.733 --> 02:52.753
I shouldn't have come to the branch.

02:54.299 --> 02:56.120
I think it's a good idea.

02:58.820 --> 03:03.596
What's good?
You came all this way to buy a book.

03:03.620 --> 03:05.600
There are
so many bookstores in the city.

03:06.380 --> 03:10.639
Consider it an experience.

03:11.500 --> 03:15.560
At that time, our school had no branch.

03:16.100 --> 03:18.079
I'm using you

03:18.579 --> 03:21.400
as an excuse to experience it.

03:41.660 --> 03:45.919
It was raining when we met once,
remember?

03:47.419 --> 03:51.639
I do. We were in the car, right?

03:53.579 --> 03:54.680
In the car.

03:58.299 --> 03:59.919
Here it comes, let's go.

04:00.780 --> 04:01.780
Wait.

04:04.139 --> 04:07.120
This bag is not waterproof, dummy.

04:08.180 --> 04:09.180
Let's go.

04:18.980 --> 04:20.519
Wait a moment!

04:21.180 --> 04:23.068
No rush, let them go first.

04:23.624 --> 04:25.788
I see there are quite a few seats there.

04:27.779 --> 04:29.279
Stand back a bit.

04:33.579 --> 04:35.560
Let's go.

04:36.904 --> 04:38.380
- I'll keep the rain off you.
- Thank you.

04:38.380 --> 04:39.932
Go ahead, you go first.

04:44.300 --> 04:47.399
- Sit towards the back, there.
- Let's sit over there.

04:59.459 --> 05:00.480
I'll help you.

05:01.139 --> 05:02.159
Thank you.

05:04.219 --> 05:05.219
All set.

05:08.820 --> 05:10.320
The rain is really heavy.

05:14.019 --> 05:15.956
- What's the matter?
- Your hair.

05:15.980 --> 05:17.719
I'll look for some tissue for you.

05:18.219 --> 05:20.199
I think I've brought some.

05:21.180 --> 05:22.839
I seem to have forgotten.

05:24.699 --> 05:26.320
- Thank you.
- Wipe it off.

05:26.820 --> 05:31.195
- You are being very meticulous.
- No, I usually don't carry tissues.

05:31.219 --> 05:34.599
I asked Mao on my way out today.
He reminded me.

05:35.540 --> 05:38.339
- Wipe it quickly. Need help?
- You go first.

05:38.339 --> 05:40.380
- I don't need it. You wipe it.
- No need, you got wet.

05:40.380 --> 05:41.980
- I'm a man, it's okay.
- You go ahead.

05:41.980 --> 05:43.360
Just wipe it quickly.

05:43.579 --> 05:45.448
It's always like this
at the beginning of a relationship.

05:45.448 --> 05:48.315
Unlike us, now we grab whatever we get.

05:48.339 --> 05:49.916
Who would dare to grab with you?

05:49.940 --> 05:51.350
- You dare to argue.
- Ouch!

05:51.350 --> 05:54.639
- Didn't you grab something?
- I did! It's all my fault!

06:00.699 --> 06:04.120
- You wipe it.
- No need. I need to check my phone.

06:08.099 --> 06:11.240
Something's up. I'll reply to it first.

06:12.060 --> 06:13.800
You still work on weekends?

06:14.500 --> 06:18.040
Entrepreneurs work
regardless of the time.

06:43.380 --> 06:45.704
(I can't talk right now.)

06:45.704 --> 06:50.360
(You guys go ahead. I'm listening.
If there's anything, I'll reply by text.)

07:07.980 --> 07:11.040
Boss, where are you?

07:13.500 --> 07:16.639
(In a place where everyone is asleep.)

07:22.779 --> 07:23.800
You're awake.

07:31.099 --> 07:33.064
Have you been replying to
WeChat messages until now?

07:33.064 --> 07:36.668
I saw you asleep, so I've been working.

07:37.259 --> 07:39.680
Boss, are you on a date?

07:41.779 --> 07:43.639
You guys go ahead. I'll mute it.

07:45.320 --> 07:46.972
(Microphone is off.)

07:48.579 --> 07:50.079
You're in a meeting?

07:51.860 --> 07:54.719
Sorry. They didn't hear what I said,
did they?

07:55.304 --> 08:00.360
You spoke when it wasn't muted,
but you don't when I'm muted, why?

08:03.620 --> 08:08.875
- I didn't know.
- It's okay. I'll continue the meeting.

08:08.899 --> 08:11.440
- You go ahead, I won't speak.
- Okay.

08:15.219 --> 08:16.219
Okay.

08:16.899 --> 08:18.159
Alright, I got it.

08:20.540 --> 08:21.540
Okay.

08:24.260 --> 08:28.839
That's it. Send me a synopsis later.
I'll hang up. Okay.

08:40.300 --> 08:41.800
Do you have a pen?

08:42.619 --> 08:43.619
Pen?

08:44.660 --> 08:46.320
Yes, wait.

08:53.859 --> 08:55.359
- Is this okay?
- Good.

09:02.664 --> 09:04.577
(Gift for Geng Xiaoxing)

09:06.834 --> 09:09.781
(Gift for Geng Xiaoxing
from Juemei Shayi)

09:11.660 --> 09:14.839
- Thank you, Mr. Juemei Shayi.
- You're welcome.

09:24.540 --> 09:28.079
I'll send you
the Yangshuo photos via Cloud Drive.

09:29.499 --> 09:34.320
- Right, the photos. Just send me.
- Good.

09:34.859 --> 09:36.079
It's sent.

09:38.379 --> 09:40.359
Received, thank you.

10:01.992 --> 10:04.260
(Welcome Home)

10:04.260 --> 10:07.016
The wind is very strong outside today.

10:07.016 --> 10:09.595
The big tree between the dormitory
and the cafeteria has fallen down.

10:09.619 --> 10:16.999
- Scared? I'll be on the phone with you.
- I'm too old to be scared of the wind.

10:19.499 --> 10:24.715
I have to go do the laundry now.
Few people use washing machines now.

10:24.739 --> 10:27.800
- Then, you go ahead.
- All right, I'm hanging up now.

10:33.540 --> 10:35.440
Is Sheng at home tonight?

10:36.699 --> 10:38.916
- She should be at home.
- That's good.

10:38.940 --> 10:41.555
There's a rain warning today.
Several subway lines are closed.

10:41.579 --> 10:45.359
It's a good thing you came back early
or you might be trapped in the branch.

10:45.459 --> 10:47.040
I'll go do laundry first.

10:53.020 --> 10:57.308
(It's raining so hard,
I wonder if he has arrived safely.)

11:30.979 --> 11:33.520
- What is he writing?
- What is he doing?

11:39.739 --> 11:44.479
- You're quite narcissistic, you know?
- What? Just practicing my signature.

11:44.579 --> 11:47.040
- Hand it over.
- What for?

11:48.140 --> 11:49.719
I'll sign one for you.

11:51.339 --> 11:53.680
What do you think?
It's better than yours, right?

11:54.379 --> 11:56.940
- A signature competition. I'll sign one.
- What are you two doing?

11:56.940 --> 11:58.440
Stop it.

11:59.140 --> 12:03.359
These cost money.
What if no one wants it?

12:05.660 --> 12:09.715
What do you mean?
Even though we're not as famous as you.

12:09.739 --> 12:11.140
But we also have our own names.

12:11.140 --> 12:13.440
Though we don't get as many chances
to sign as you do.

12:13.440 --> 12:15.996
But we should at least have the right
to entertain ourselves.

12:16.020 --> 12:18.075
- Isn't what you just said too much?
- Too much.

12:18.099 --> 12:20.475
- Is there something going on?
- We...

12:20.499 --> 12:21.999
How did you come back?

12:22.619 --> 12:25.756
- How come you're back already?
- Why shouldn't I come back?

12:25.780 --> 12:28.470
Imagine how romantic it would be
to be trapped by a heavy rain,

12:28.470 --> 12:31.320
spending an entire night
in the classroom at the branch.

12:31.979 --> 12:35.116
Mao, wait a minute.
Please make it clear. Who?

12:35.140 --> 12:37.760
Right. You make it clear. Who?

12:39.020 --> 12:40.220
Who?

12:41.219 --> 12:43.280
- Nobody.
- Nobody.

12:44.540 --> 12:47.355
- Fine.
- I'm going home. You guys chat.

12:47.379 --> 12:49.599
- Speaking half way.
- Really pointless.

12:52.328 --> 12:53.760
Juemei.

12:54.260 --> 12:55.999
You're going a bit too far.

12:56.060 --> 12:58.636
- My uncle won't print them for you.
- Why?

12:58.660 --> 13:01.315
- No, I'm signing them all today.
- Wang Ke.

13:01.339 --> 13:02.036
Give it all to me.

13:02.060 --> 13:03.916
- Get out.
- I'll help you, wait for me!

13:03.940 --> 13:06.879
- What's wrong? Leave me some.
- Both of you, out.

13:09.859 --> 13:13.760
How is it? Interesting?
A preserved project of our studio.

13:13.859 --> 13:18.835
They are all quite lovely in private.
But Mr. Mo and Mr. Feng rarely come by.

13:18.859 --> 13:22.520
- Now we barely see them once a week.
- They are busy.

13:24.579 --> 13:29.595
You have missed our best times.
Everyone was here in our school days.

13:29.619 --> 13:32.959
This place was really busy at that time.

13:42.260 --> 13:43.760
H-Hurry!

13:45.660 --> 13:52.920
Sheng, it's raining so heavily.
Where are you now? Be very careful.

13:53.499 --> 13:55.675
I am at a friend's house now.

13:55.699 --> 13:59.636
It's too dangerous now.
I'll go home when it cools down.

13:59.660 --> 14:05.075
- Just wait. Call me if you're scared.
- What's there to be scared of?

14:05.099 --> 14:08.595
You all mustn't go out.
It's too dangerous now.

14:08.619 --> 14:12.719
- Alright, you don't go out either.
- Okay, goodbye.

14:34.739 --> 14:36.239
- Dr. Mo.
- Hello.

14:39.860 --> 14:41.579
- (Hello, listeners.)
- Dr. Mo, you have finished the surgery.

14:41.579 --> 14:43.876
(Let's focus on the weather.)

14:43.900 --> 14:48.116
(Some areas of our city have been affected
by the heavy rain cloud cluster.)

14:48.140 --> 14:50.620
(It is expected
that the heavy rainfall will continue.)

14:50.900 --> 14:52.600
(Ancheng weather station issued)

14:52.600 --> 14:55.435
(an orange warning for
heavy rain at 21:00 tonight.)

14:55.459 --> 14:57.075
(Please be prepared.)

14:57.099 --> 14:59.509
(Once again. Some areas of our city)

14:59.509 --> 15:03.156
(have been affected by
the heavy rain cloud cluster.)

15:03.180 --> 15:05.520
(It is expected
that the heavy rainfall will continue.)

15:07.540 --> 15:13.320
You're off work early today,
but this rain makes it hard to drive.

15:13.859 --> 15:14.959
It's okay.

15:15.619 --> 15:20.475
I can take the subway.
There will be few people in the subway.

15:20.499 --> 15:24.599
We are in the branch office, okay?
Both subway lines are shut down.

15:25.099 --> 15:27.800
- I'm afraid you can't take the subway.
- Yeah, that's true.

15:27.859 --> 15:31.156
It's okay. I'll wait,
and have something to eat.

15:31.180 --> 15:34.099
Okay, then, Dr. Mo, you take a rest.
I'll go to work first.

15:34.099 --> 15:35.879
- Okay, go ahead.
- All right.

16:31.619 --> 16:33.839
(Are you okay in the hospital?)

16:36.379 --> 16:37.680
Just finished a surgery.

16:42.180 --> 16:44.220
(Is it convenient
to have a voice chat now?)

16:50.180 --> 16:51.199
Hello?

16:51.900 --> 16:56.119
- Where are you, the branch or the main?
- At the branch.

16:56.300 --> 16:58.856
I had three surgeries in the afternoon
after the outpatient clinic

16:58.856 --> 17:00.796
and I have been working until now.

17:00.820 --> 17:02.520
Have you eaten something?

17:02.779 --> 17:05.319
Youjian river snails rice noodles.
[*Youjian means once again]

17:06.500 --> 17:11.119
Your mom mentioned Yangshuo, Guilin today.
It reminded me of those days.

17:11.780 --> 17:13.896
I found a cup of
river snails rice noodles in the cupboard,

17:13.896 --> 17:15.516
so I'm making it.

17:16.099 --> 17:17.200
It's my dinner.

17:17.899 --> 17:21.960
Youjian. I was just thinking
what brand Youjian is.

17:24.780 --> 17:27.919
Are you home?
You didn't get stuck outside, did you?

17:30.060 --> 17:31.639
I'm already home.

17:33.220 --> 17:37.052
You're making me hungry.
Wait, let me to get something to eat.

17:37.579 --> 17:39.919
Okay. Going to the kitchen for food?

17:40.500 --> 17:44.200
Right, to the kitchen,
wait for me to go downstairs.

18:24.232 --> 18:25.980
(Are you on duty at the hospital?)

18:26.408 --> 18:28.439
(Yes, I just switched shifts.)

18:29.864 --> 18:32.252
(Help me check the supermarket
across the street.)

18:33.384 --> 18:34.520
(Supermarket?)

18:36.339 --> 18:39.879
(To see if there is a girl trapped.
And take care of yourself.)

18:42.300 --> 18:43.599
(Girl?)

18:45.419 --> 18:48.800
(Just take a look from a distance.
Don't go inside and scare her.)

18:55.624 --> 18:57.276
(Okay, right away.)

18:58.248 --> 18:59.339
(Sheng)

18:59.339 --> 19:05.480
- Found something good to eat?
- No, my mom doesn't like leftovers.

19:06.619 --> 19:08.320
I've discovered something good.

19:09.980 --> 19:13.560
Can you believe my mom actually bought
some river snails rice noodles at home?

19:15.899 --> 19:17.280
What a coincidence.

19:18.020 --> 19:19.040
Right.

19:53.379 --> 19:57.679
- Why are you not speaking?
- It's ready, I'm eating now.

19:58.339 --> 20:01.879
The taste is okay, but of course,
it's not as good as the ones cooked.

20:02.312 --> 20:05.610
That's true. The river snails rice noodles
we had in Guilin

20:05.610 --> 20:07.756
had more than
a dozen different toppings.

20:07.780 --> 20:10.839
And the snails were all in big chunks.

20:15.139 --> 20:17.200
Eat slowly. Wait for me.

20:20.460 --> 20:24.599
Okay, I'll wait for you.
I've placed the fork on the box.

20:32.139 --> 20:35.839
Then let's make a video call,
so we can see each other eat.

20:38.300 --> 20:39.639
I can't right now.

20:40.139 --> 20:41.676
My grandfather is still awake.

20:41.700 --> 20:46.599
It would be bad if he comes and sees it,
and my parents are both here today.

20:48.099 --> 20:49.099
Okay.

20:54.020 --> 20:57.040
Reporting to Mr. Mo,
I'm going to add seasonings now.

20:57.859 --> 21:02.079
- I've already had two bites.
- Then I need to speed up.

21:10.740 --> 21:14.800
- Reporting to Mr. Mo, I'm going to eat.
- Then let's begin.

21:42.339 --> 21:45.639
- I think this spiciness is just right.
- So is mine.

22:06.820 --> 22:10.599
Hey, open the door! Please!

22:11.939 --> 22:13.720
There are guests. I need to hang up.

22:15.379 --> 22:18.399
Open the door, please.

22:23.500 --> 22:27.676
- Sorry, we've closed.
- Do you have raincoats? I want one.

22:27.700 --> 22:30.040
Raincoat. The rain is too heavy.

22:30.619 --> 22:33.320
- My umbrella is broken.
- Come in.

22:37.260 --> 22:38.899
Miss, do you have any raincoats?

22:38.899 --> 22:41.280
- You need raincoat? Please wait.
- Yes.

22:46.659 --> 22:48.919
- Here is the raincoat.
- Thank you.

22:49.899 --> 22:52.040
- How much is it?
- Twenty-five.

22:52.339 --> 22:55.159
- I'll pay you. Scan the code, okay?
- Over here.

22:59.220 --> 23:00.599
I can't turn on my phone.

23:01.260 --> 23:05.196
- It's okay, forget it. It's for you.
- It got wet and broke down.

23:05.220 --> 23:08.060
- Then I'll pay you tomorrow, okay?
- Okay.

23:08.060 --> 23:10.520
Thank you then, I'll leave.

23:10.820 --> 23:12.240
The rain is too heavy.

23:15.859 --> 23:19.835
- Thank you, I'll pay you tomorrow.
- Be careful.

23:19.859 --> 23:22.359
- Thank you, you can go back.
- Be safe.

23:31.700 --> 23:36.040
Get in! Let me help you!

23:37.768 --> 23:40.740
- This rain.
- Thank you. Thank you for this.

23:40.740 --> 23:41.716
Don't mention it.

23:41.740 --> 23:45.079
- May I ask what you want to buy?
- I'm not buying anything.

23:47.300 --> 23:49.599
Then what are you...?

23:50.859 --> 23:55.356
I'm taking a look.

23:55.912 --> 23:59.320
- Taking a look of?
- Of... you.

24:01.419 --> 24:05.520
- Of me?
- Of you.

24:10.260 --> 24:11.399
Well...

24:13.339 --> 24:15.639
Let me tell you the truth.

24:16.500 --> 24:19.716
My name is Zhang Lele. I am a doctor
from the hospital across the street.

24:19.740 --> 24:23.359
Mo Qingcheng is my colleague.
He asked me to come and check on you.

24:29.899 --> 24:33.399
- You scared me to death.
- You scared me to death. Sorry.

24:34.020 --> 24:35.580
How does he know I am here?

24:36.104 --> 24:40.800
He just knows. He is so smart.

24:43.060 --> 24:45.500
- I'm sorry for the trouble.
- It's okay.

24:45.500 --> 24:48.075
You're all soaked.
Let me get you a towel to wipe yourself.

24:48.099 --> 24:50.560
Thank you.

24:54.579 --> 24:57.520
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

24:59.619 --> 25:03.200
Uh, there's something
I'm quite curious about.

25:03.379 --> 25:08.800
Dr. Mo specifically asked me
to check on you on such a rainy day.

25:08.899 --> 25:13.119
You two must be close.
Are you his girlfriend?

25:17.339 --> 25:21.980
I've done the mission Dr. Mo gave me.

25:21.980 --> 25:23.996
I still have a shift,
so I'll head back first.

25:24.020 --> 25:27.595
Wait, let me get you a pair of slippers.
Your shoes are all wet.

25:27.619 --> 25:31.399
No need, sister-in-law,
I'll have him reimburse me.

25:31.980 --> 25:36.200
- What about food? Do you want to some?
- There's some in the lounge, I'm leaving.

25:37.139 --> 25:38.139
Then,

25:39.240 --> 25:40.960
be careful.

25:41.220 --> 25:45.756
- Be careful!
- Lock the door. Don't open it for anyone.

25:45.780 --> 25:47.800
- Take care!
- I'm off.

26:03.939 --> 26:06.040
Your colleague was here just now.

26:06.740 --> 26:09.119
You really can't be fooled,
you guess it all.

26:12.579 --> 26:13.800
Has he gone back?

26:14.540 --> 26:17.760
Yes, he said he has a night shift
and went back.

26:30.220 --> 26:31.875
- Hello?
- Dr. Mo.

26:31.899 --> 26:35.760
Our sister-in-law is already safe
in the supermarket.

26:36.139 --> 26:40.280
Mission completed successfully.
I am reliable, right?

26:40.500 --> 26:44.399
- You're being reliable, thanks.
- Just saying thank you is not enough.

26:44.460 --> 26:49.200
I braved heavy rain to do you a favor.
You must reward me well.

26:50.120 --> 26:51.260
Well...

26:51.780 --> 26:54.676
When did you start
to enjoy doing such stealthy things?

26:54.700 --> 26:57.555
Is she the clam girl
from the phone call?

26:57.579 --> 27:00.919
When did you start dating?
How come you never told me?

27:01.260 --> 27:02.720
I'll tell you later.

27:06.700 --> 27:11.040
- Dr. Mo, are you leaving? It's raining.
- I know.

27:11.820 --> 27:13.399
My girlfriend is still outside.

27:14.540 --> 27:16.520
Wait a bit, it's rainy outside.

28:12.179 --> 28:16.399
The rain is pouring down heavily today.
It just doesn't stop.

28:18.099 --> 28:23.679
Can't get delivery in this weather,
I'm hungry, and Chef Qiang isn't here.

28:24.260 --> 28:25.320
I'll cook.

28:26.139 --> 28:32.800
You'll make me doubt the food,
and then doubt humanity itself, okay?

28:33.740 --> 28:37.399
- Where did you copy that line from?
- It was improvised on the spot.

28:53.540 --> 28:58.399
Little girl would be scared
to sleep alone in this weather.

28:59.220 --> 29:05.436
Who are you talking about? Doudou?
She is a force to reckon with,

29:05.460 --> 29:07.060
the real boss behind
The Perfect Voice Studio.

29:07.060 --> 29:07.956
What does she fear?

29:07.980 --> 29:10.056
She is recording
the rain sounds outside,

29:10.056 --> 29:12.380
saying that this lifelike sound
can be of use later.

29:13.070 --> 29:14.159
That's her.

29:32.659 --> 29:33.760
Mao.

29:34.500 --> 29:39.480
Can you open that project for me later?
I'll stay up and finish tomorrow's work.

29:40.339 --> 29:44.796
I'll just open the project for you.
Everything else is none of my business.

29:44.820 --> 29:45.839
Okay.

29:51.780 --> 29:56.079
See? Someone can't sleep
because he hasn't sent a WeChat message.

29:58.379 --> 30:00.119
Too young.

30:01.060 --> 30:02.839
Still too young.

30:07.740 --> 30:12.960
When is Doudou coming back?
I miss her so much.

30:14.500 --> 30:16.155
You are acting strange today.

30:16.179 --> 30:19.399
You mentioned Doudou many times.
What? Do you miss her?

30:19.700 --> 30:22.599
You have been brothers for many years.
You can't be like this.

30:24.260 --> 30:28.436
Apart from Mr. Qiang Qingci,
Doudou cooks the best food. I'm hungry.

30:28.460 --> 30:30.119
Hungry, do you understand?

30:30.740 --> 30:32.079
I will try it myself.

30:35.260 --> 30:36.480
I don't believe it.

30:38.099 --> 30:40.399
No, I don't agree.

31:06.740 --> 31:10.159
How is this song getting scarier
the more it plays?

31:16.616 --> 31:20.488
♪ Where should I start
about millions of dawns and dusks ♪

31:20.488 --> 31:24.774
♪ Depict a stroke of rain
before the mountain, stars beyond the sky ♪

31:25.160 --> 31:29.660
♪ Bit by bit, it outlines
yesterday and today ♪

31:30.899 --> 31:32.599
I'm going over there to take a look.

31:35.176 --> 31:38.984
♪ The rain and fog
over the mountains are intriguing ♪

31:38.984 --> 31:43.432
♪ It seems I can't get enough of seeing
The once inexhaustible journey ♪

31:43.432 --> 31:46.184
♪ On this journey, the stars accompany me
along thousands of miles ♪

31:46.184 --> 31:48.456
♪ I walk down with you ♪

31:48.456 --> 31:52.379
♪ Spending dawns and dusks together
for a hundred years ♪

31:52.379 --> 31:54.599
Stop, pull over the car.

31:55.016 --> 31:57.415
♪ When the clouds are low, it rains ♪

31:57.415 --> 32:02.024
♪ I was moved
when you were singing softly ♪

32:02.024 --> 32:06.760
♪ Since then, I hear stars every night
And rains at midnight ♪

32:06.760 --> 32:11.676
♪ I could hear you
among millions of voices ♪

32:12.136 --> 32:13.776
Let's have something to eat.

32:13.800 --> 32:16.346
♪ I hear your monologue ♪

32:16.346 --> 32:20.458
♪ Saying I miss you so much ♪

32:20.458 --> 32:23.176
♪ Like knowing the implied meaning
of a picture ♪

32:23.176 --> 32:25.736
♪ Knowing your happiness and sadness ♪

32:25.736 --> 32:29.096
♪ Lightly falling
outside and inside the dream ♪

32:29.096 --> 32:33.036
♪ With you in this life ♪

32:47.164 --> 32:52.272
♪ There is a voice
that soaks the green plums ♪

32:53.116 --> 32:58.064
♪ There is a voice
that wrinkles the blue sky ♪

32:58.994 --> 33:03.283
♪ Shedding an invisible spring rain ♪

33:03.283 --> 33:09.482
♪ The world is drunk at a timid moment ♪

33:10.808 --> 33:16.176
♪ We talk and laugh
as if we are holding hands ♪

33:17.116 --> 33:23.164
♪ We stay silent
like falling behind the sunset ♪

33:23.164 --> 33:27.760
♪ That moment is still lingering ♪

33:27.820 --> 33:31.839
(With the lights on at this time,
everything can be seen inside.)

33:32.339 --> 33:35.240
(Turn off the lights.
I need to turn off the lights.)

33:35.880 --> 33:42.544
♪ You flow through my heart like a river ♪

33:42.568 --> 33:48.592
♪ Echoing with the constant gentleness
of the bright moon ♪

33:48.616 --> 33:51.624
♪ Looking back
among fleeting and everlasting moments ♪

33:51.624 --> 33:54.512
♪ We embrace as we look around ♪

33:54.536 --> 34:00.156
♪ Each sound is a promise of forever
to a lifetime ♪

34:00.660 --> 34:02.359
(I'm snacking.)

34:09.100 --> 34:12.200
You feel like eating? Then I'm relieved.

34:16.180 --> 34:17.720
Where are you?

34:22.419 --> 34:23.600
I'm at the hospital.

34:24.660 --> 34:27.359
You must not go anywhere
at a time like this.

34:31.899 --> 34:33.160
Got it.

34:46.260 --> 34:48.919
Sheng, are you scared?

34:54.059 --> 34:55.680
A little bit.

35:15.419 --> 35:21.959
Aren't you sleeping? Aren't you tired?
I'm fine, you don't need to call me.

35:24.180 --> 35:25.600
I can't sleep.

35:26.979 --> 35:30.200
You're also scared of the storm?

35:32.580 --> 35:37.959
You said that you used to
listen to my audio dramas to sleep.

35:38.859 --> 35:40.320
In high school.

35:41.180 --> 35:47.280
Then we don't hang up tonight.
We can chat until you fall asleep.

35:48.459 --> 35:51.919
Or, if there is really nothing to chat,

35:52.620 --> 35:54.240
I can also recite the script.

35:54.888 --> 35:59.399
The lines of the audio drama you like.
Tell me and I will read them for you.

35:59.939 --> 36:03.359
Or some lines that I can remember,
I can recite them directly for you.

36:04.260 --> 36:07.080
All you have to do is talk.
Anything will do.

36:13.459 --> 36:14.908
There is a fire truck?

36:16.019 --> 36:17.559
I suppose so.

36:18.539 --> 36:22.039
Fire departments are called out
more frequently in this kind of weather.

36:41.300 --> 36:43.879
- Play a song?
- Sure.

37:16.808 --> 37:22.192
♪ Turning the years into a drifting boat ♪

37:22.216 --> 37:27.424
♪ Sailing through
the tumult and winding sorrow ♪

37:27.496 --> 37:33.000
♪ I fear that the past will be crushed
by the coming cold wind ♪

37:33.000 --> 37:38.969
♪ And stirred into
a piece of tranquil river water ♪

37:41.096 --> 37:46.492
♪ Touching the crack with my fingertips ♪

37:46.568 --> 37:51.888
♪ I dare not look at the haggard faces
and gray hair in the mirror ♪

37:51.912 --> 37:57.256
♪ After many years,
the longing remains as sharp ♪

37:57.256 --> 38:02.672
♪ And our shadows are thinner ♪

38:02.696 --> 38:06.088
♪ Grinding the memories into ink ♪

38:06.088 --> 38:08.680
♪ And writing them on the paper ♪

38:08.680 --> 38:10.760
♪ The mirror and the person
are both gone ♪

38:10.760 --> 38:13.512
♪ Where could I ask for the return date ♪

38:13.512 --> 38:16.750
♪ The bronze mirror shatters at farewell ♪

38:16.750 --> 38:18.792
♪ It's hard to convey the lovesickness ♪

38:18.792 --> 38:23.126
♪ Over millions of miles ♪

38:24.040 --> 38:27.656
♪ I laugh at the fame
and wealth of my life ♪

38:27.656 --> 38:29.672
♪ I picture it as a flower in the mirror ♪

38:29.672 --> 38:34.694
♪ It's hard to rival
a cup of tea in your hand ♪

38:34.694 --> 38:36.392
♪ We drink from the same cup ♪

38:36.392 --> 38:38.280
♪ And we share joy and sorrow ♪

38:38.280 --> 38:41.031
♪ We drink down the past memories ♪

38:41.031 --> 38:45.832
♪ Being together from morning till night ♪

38:45.832 --> 38:49.064
♪ Or alone in the corner of the world ♪

38:49.064 --> 38:51.320
♪ Frost whitens the hair
in front of the forehead ♪

38:51.320 --> 38:56.264
♪ Looking at the world, where is my home ♪

38:56.264 --> 38:58.998
♪ I wish the clear frost
glitter in the moonlight ♪

38:58.998 --> 39:02.640
♪ Reflecting the couple in the mirror ♪

39:02.664 --> 39:05.756
♪ Return with you ♪

39:11.899 --> 39:15.399
Hello, are you okay?

39:15.939 --> 39:18.039
I'm fine, can you open the door for me?

39:21.979 --> 39:24.280
Sheng, open the door.

39:34.059 --> 39:35.720
How come you are here?

39:42.220 --> 39:44.479
- Hurry in!
- Come in quickly!

39:45.100 --> 39:47.479
- Let me.
- I'll turn on the lights first.

39:54.499 --> 39:56.600
You...

39:58.419 --> 39:59.519
Stunned?

40:01.620 --> 40:05.160
There's a bit of traffic.
Or I could be half an hour earlier.

40:05.339 --> 40:06.919
Where did you come from?

40:08.140 --> 40:09.600
I came from the branch.

40:11.220 --> 40:14.800
Look, you're completely soaked.
Let me get a towel for you.

40:16.780 --> 40:18.039
Wait for me.

40:27.620 --> 40:31.200
It's not safe for a girl
to sleep in a supermarket

40:31.979 --> 40:33.120
at this hour.

40:36.580 --> 40:42.120
Bad people hide during torrential rain.
It's not safe for them either.

40:44.100 --> 40:45.100
Let me.

40:50.220 --> 40:51.220
Thank you.

40:55.019 --> 40:58.999
Did your shoes get wet?
Should I find you a pair of slippers?

40:59.339 --> 41:01.959
It's okay. No need, I changed them
before getting in the car.

41:04.419 --> 41:06.600
- Give it to me.
- Okay.

41:10.059 --> 41:12.188
I suddenly feel
that it's not bad living here.

41:12.939 --> 41:14.559
With food and drinks.

41:15.339 --> 41:17.919
And you can eat whatever you like.

41:18.539 --> 41:22.039
Okay, I'll pay
for whatever you've opened tonight.

41:22.979 --> 41:26.200
Why would you pay
at my family's supermarket?

41:26.339 --> 41:29.999
You're keeping me company tonight,
so I should be the one treating you.

41:30.140 --> 41:32.479
Eat as you please, it's all on me.

41:37.459 --> 41:38.600
I know.

41:40.660 --> 41:41.680
This.

41:42.220 --> 41:43.220
Let me.

41:48.660 --> 41:49.660
Thank you.

42:01.979 --> 42:04.479
Won't you be scared here alone at night?

42:06.700 --> 42:08.680
I was actually quite scared just now.

42:08.680 --> 42:11.515
It's dark outside.
Only our supermarket was lit up.

42:11.539 --> 42:13.039
I got scared immediately.

42:13.039 --> 42:16.640
It's safer to turn off the lights
at this time, right?

42:19.059 --> 42:20.320
Well analyzed.

42:21.339 --> 42:24.872
Also, when the music is
playing publicly and the store is empty,

42:24.872 --> 42:26.796
the louder the music is,
the more frightening it gets.

42:26.820 --> 42:29.160
Putting on headphones instead,
calms me down.

42:33.580 --> 42:36.120
You're all wet. What should I do?

42:37.660 --> 42:40.355
Do you have raincoats or umbrellas?

42:40.379 --> 42:42.796
I have clean clothes in my car.
I can bring them in to change.

42:42.820 --> 42:44.800
Yes, here.

43:36.008 --> 43:41.488
♪ Turning the years into a drifting boat ♪

43:41.512 --> 43:46.864
♪ Sailing through
the tumult and winding sorrow ♪

43:46.888 --> 43:52.232
♪ I fear that the past will be crushed
by the coming cold wind ♪

43:52.232 --> 43:57.953
♪ And stirred into
a piece of tranquil river water ♪

44:00.392 --> 44:05.800
♪ Touching the crack with my fingertips ♪

44:05.800 --> 44:11.120
♪ I dare not look at the haggard faces
and gray hair in the mirror ♪

44:11.144 --> 44:16.488
♪ After many years,
the longing remains as sharp ♪

44:16.488 --> 44:21.928
♪ And our shadows are thinner ♪

44:21.928 --> 44:25.160
♪ Grinding the memories into ink ♪

44:25.160 --> 44:27.912
♪ And writing them on the paper ♪

44:27.912 --> 44:30.068
♪ The mirror and the person
are both gone ♪

44:30.068 --> 44:32.456
♪ Where could I ask for the return date ♪

44:32.456 --> 44:35.944
♪ The bronze mirror shatters at farewell ♪

44:35.944 --> 44:38.165
♪ It's hard to convey the lovesickness ♪

44:38.165 --> 44:42.643
♪ Over millions of miles ♪

44:43.208 --> 44:46.920
♪ I laugh at the fame
and wealth of my life ♪

44:46.920 --> 44:48.878
♪ I picture it as a flower in the mirror ♪

44:48.878 --> 44:53.864
♪ It's hard to rival
a cup of tea in your hand ♪

44:53.864 --> 44:55.592
♪ We drink from the same cup ♪

44:55.592 --> 44:57.512
♪ And we share joy and sorrow ♪

44:57.512 --> 45:00.360
♪ We drink down the past memories ♪

45:00.360 --> 45:04.680
♪ Being together from morning till night ♪

45:04.680 --> 45:08.327
♪ Or alone in the corner of the world ♪

45:08.327 --> 45:10.440
♪ Frost whitens the hair
in front of the forehead ♪

45:10.440 --> 45:15.542
♪ Looking at the world, where is my home ♪

45:15.542 --> 45:17.928
♪ I wish the clear frost
glitter in the moonlight ♪

45:17.928 --> 45:21.928
♪ Reflecting the couple in the mirror ♪

45:21.928 --> 45:27.004
♪ Return with you ♪

45:27.752 --> 45:33.148
♪ After being separated for half a life ♪
